<br>
I've talked to someone who is willing to MQ it,  but they want at least 20kpp.   Only thing I have that's worth close to that is a Tranquil staff on my monk, and if you've ever used one, you know why it's hard to give it up.<br>
<br>
Questions - Is there a better way to get the Kedge Robe without having to drag a group down to Phinney every 12 hours ?   It took another rogue in our guild about 8 tries before one dropped.   I've heard of a lot worse.<br>
<br>
How often does the robe drop in Kith, and is it any easier to get ?<br>
<br>
Thanks for any info. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueelyen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eelyen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 1:10:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> I really liked my Kedge Robe, but a friend offered me a bone clasped girled in exchange for my robe and my oakleaf girdle.  I took him up on the offer :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uteramenor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teramenor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 2:53:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> There is a better way than killing Phinigel. The Coercer in Kithicor can drop the Kedge robe; reports vary from 1 in 3 to 1 in 5 attempts. It is possible for a 60 ranger to single-pull her from the house. The other DEs in the house can ALSO DROP THE KEDGE ROBE (I saw one drop off of Brigadier G`tav, I think his name is, during my General party), but the Coercer is the easiest to kill and has it the most often. The respawn time on the house mobs is 1 day. You can kill the Coercer with 1 well-balanced 55+ group, but you'll need 2 groups to safely kill each of the rest of the Dark Elves, as they are mostly strong melee types, and the Coercer is a puny enchantress.<br>
<br>
- Rohane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwillaani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Willaani</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 3:13:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> It'n not worth paying anything for the Kedge Robe to MQ (unless you have the cash and wanna blow it)... just get 2 solid groups together and wipe out the DE camp in Kith every chance you get because sooner or later, one of the DE's will drop a Kedge Robe for you.  And as posted above, it is more common from the Coercer to have it than the rest, but I personally got mine from the War Priestess (what a surprise that was) and it was the 4th DE camp clearing that I held (respawn time is 8 hours, not 1 day).<br>
<br>
Phinny is real stingy with the Kedge Robe so I suggest that you avoid him and just kill the DE's (and I mean ALL of them). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utideni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tideni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 7:30:40 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> I agree with Willaani.<br>
<br>
Waiting for a kedge robe to drop is like waiting for water to boil - after you get it you'll be glad you didn't let your friend gouge you out of 20k. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulimbas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>limbas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 10:49:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1>    I have killed Phin five times and he has dropped the Robe four times....I have killed about 24 of those dark elves, including the coercer three times, and have never seen her or any of the other DEs drop the Kedge robe.  Phin is quite easy honestly, as Druids can help out by charming the Swirlspine Guardians, which are generally the downfall of most Phin raids.  Even did Phin without an enchanter and only one damage dealer (52 rogue)(not recommended).  The other good thing about Phin is you can make ALOT of other people happy by getting their epic pieces from Phin too, cause it is a real pain to see the bard spine drop cause someone would not let the spine be looted <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
   The only plus I see to the Coercer is that she will be wearing the kedge robe when she has it, so that is always a good thing.  Just take two groups to Kedge, kill Phin, go to Kith kill all the DEs, 13 hours after you killed Phin, go back to Kedge and clear the seahorses at about 13 hours 15 minutes after you killed phin, then pull any guardians that happen to spawn, then Phin will spawn about 13 and a half hours after you killed him.  Go back to Kith, wash, rinse, repeat.  Then if you just get mad, Kedge MQs go for 15k on Xegony, but finding someone you can trust is the hard part...But I have seen people offering RBGs for a MQ.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchantre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chantre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 11:13:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info Limbas - my problem is getting two groups organized and headed there before another group beats me.  The last 7 times we killed phinny, I think the drops were pretty rare, for all epics.  You had an awesome run of good luck I believe.  Hopefully mine will be too.<br>
<br>
Can anyone else speak to how often they have seen them drop off the Coercer and Co. ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaklek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JAKLE k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 11:25:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> me and 3 friends to the DE's all the time.<br>
provided we get there during the day we can kill the advisior and coerser in about 20 min  and be gone. our group is 58 warrior 55 rogue 52 cleric 60 chanter. this is so easy and id say odd's are one in 3 or one in 4. this beats going to form a phine raid anyday, plus we havent seen one yet but they can drop rbg's<br>
<br>
just a tip the way we split them is dispell her and train to RV zone then when trainer zones they all go back but she stops to rebuff the buffs you disspelled. other key thing is all mellee MUST click thier first buff off so when she slows ya someone can just dispell it, 70% slow sucks. the rest of the tactics you can figure out yourself <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzardossk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zardossk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 12:23:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge Robe - what's it worth to MQ ?</span><hr size=1> Here was my strat on Phinny...<br>
<br>
My guild assembled and killed him twice, both times NO epic peices dropped.  So a wiz guildie and I camped out in KK till he spawned again, then we alerted other big guilds that needed him for certain epic peices and when they came, we asked if we could help out for a chance at the peices we needed, 9 times outta 10 they said yes, after doing this for about 4 or 5 spawns of him I got a robe, but the wiz peice still hasnt dropped and my wiz friend is going insane <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
If your gonna attempt this make sure to have a fishbone earring or rebreather, and invis potions just in case, and a map of KK or know your way thru there good...<br>
<br>
Hope this helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
